This paper deals with machine learning and graph representation learning, which are core topics in the field of computer science. Specifically, it focuses on pre-training Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for molecular property and protein function prediction, which are applications of machine learning in science and medicine. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
